When a Chinese monk broke into a hidden cave in 1900, he uncovered one of the worldÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s great literary secrets: a time capsule from the ancient Silk Road. Inside, scrolls were piled from floor to ceiling, undisturbed for a thousand years. The gem within was the Diamond Sutra of AD 868. This key Buddhist teaching, made 500 years before Gutenberg inked his press, is the worldÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s oldest printed book.
